{"id":"349005058_Exploration_and_Optimization_in_Crystal_Structure_Prediction_Combining_Basin_Hopping_with_Quasi-Random_Sampling","abstract":"We describe the implementation of a Monte Carlo basin hopping (BH) global optimization procedure for the prediction of molecular crystal structures. The BH method is combined with quasi-random (QR) structure generation in a hybrid method for crystal structure prediction, QR-BH, which combines the low-discrepancy sampling provided by QR sequences with BH efficiency at locating low energy structures. Through tests on a set of single-component molecular crystals and co-crystals, we demonstrate that QR-BH provides faster location of low energy structures than pure QR sampling, while maintaining the efficient location of higher energy structures that are important for identifying important polymorphs.","authors":["Shiyue Yang","Graeme Day"],"meta":["February 2021Journal of Chemical Theory and Computation 17(3)","DOI:10.1021/acs.jctc.0c01101"],"references":["342625119_Structure_prediction_of_crystals_surfaces_and_nano-particles","340059014_Photocatalytic_Proton_Reduction_by_a_Computationally_Identified_Molecular_Hydrogen-Bonded_Framework","335078707_A_Prolific_Solvate_Former_Galunisertib_Under_the_Pressure_of_Crystal_Structure_Prediction_Produces_Ten_Diverse_Polymorphs","326796003_Successful_Computationally_Directed_Templating_of_Metastable_Pharmaceutical_Polymorphs","305382418_How_important_is_thermal_expansion_for_predicting_molecular_crystal_structures_and_thermochemistry_at_finite_temperatures","303386854_Report_on_the_Sixth_Blind_Test_of_Organic_Crystal-Structure_Prediction_Methods","299572828_The_Cambridge_Structural_Database","282152353_Facts_and_fictions_about_polymorphism","274013085_Static_and_lattice_vibrational_energy_differences_between_polymorphs","235760866_Current_approaches_to_predicting_molecular_organic_crystal_structures","225050049_Constrained_evolutionary_algorithm_for_structure_prediction_of_molecular_crystals